Careers in Africa has released it latest Employer Choice ranking – focusing on the companies that African professionals most want to work for. The ranking is based on a study completed by more than 20,000 African professionals, answering around 50 questions each on what makes a great employer, what they like about specific employers, and how they feel in their current role. While the report represented every one of the continent’s 54 markets, a large number of companies on the list were founded or have headquarters based in South Africa. These include big names across a wide variety of business sectors – such as MTN, MultiChoice, South African Airways, and FNB. You can find a list of the top 10 companies, as well as a ranking of some of the more notable South African-based companies below. Notable companies in South Africa Read: 5 things McKinsey is doing to try salvage its reputation in South Africa